    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-03-01T09:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-03-01T09:00:00-05:00" n="125"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d125">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72112/7601a</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_PWH1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Page</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-03-01T09:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 1, 1918, 9 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>6725. For <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_SLP1">Sheldon</persName> [from
                        <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_FPj1">Fuller</persName>, War Trade
                    Board]:</p>
                <p>No. 139. <persName>Frothingham</persName>. Referring Embassy’s 8745, February 20,
                    7 p.m., your 183.</p>
                <p>Plan arranged with only British and French includes joint consideration Allied
                    representatives in each country listed. Review Spanish and Moroccan names Paris
                    or London. Review rest Europe in London. Report results and reasons
                    simultaneously to War Trade Board, British Embassy, and French High Commission,
                    Washington, <pb facs="0188" n="1022" xml:id="pg_1022"/> for final United States
                    decision. Following cable sent United States missions, Greece and neutral
                    European countries except Spain and Switzerland: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>Confer with Allied colleagues before recommending changes in enemy
                            trading list and, if agreement results from conference, report in
                            duplicate simultaneously to State Department and Ensign Frothingham,
                            United States Embassy, London, decisions and reasons. If disagreement
                            results, send your opinion and variant opinions of colleagues with
                            reasons. In each case give nationality and residence of person or
                            association recommended for addition to or removal from list. Repeat to
                            consuls.</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <list>
                            <item>
                                <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_FPj1">Fuller</persName>
                            </item>
                            <item>
                                <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_LR1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </item>
                        </list>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
